<br>
If you try and pull 4 raptors to Chessboard you will likely end up dead a lot, lose some of the raptors, or lose your camp quite often to others out there. <p><p align=left><font face="Trebuchet MS, Tahoma" size="1"><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=6031>Ligge</a> - Changing Tide CoGuildleader<br><font color=green><a href="http://pub17.ezboard.com/beqguide">Changing Tide's Boards</a><b> || </b><a href="http://pub2.ezboard.com/bthefolk">The Folk's Boards</a></font><br><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/changingtide/images/inpom.jpg><br><b>"You must be the change you wish to see in the world." - Mahatma Ghandi</b><br>"Never argue with an idiot. They drag you down to their level then beat you with experience."</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uduggallmunnybaggs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Duggall Munnybaggs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/1/01 12:54:59 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> What I did</span><hr size=1> Well, when I was still hunting raptors, I did it both ways, on the little rocks and pulling to the CB island.<br>
<br>
Quadding on the small island is much easier than on the big island, because there is only one wanderer, and one vicious.  Snare the wanderer, then snare 3 more (which usually includes the vicious), round em up and quad em on either the north or south beach, depending on which ones you snared.<br>
<br>
Quadding on the east side of the big island is easier than quadding on the west.  Cammo and watch the wanderers.  When they are both available, snare em and get 2 more and quad up and down the east side of the big island.<br>
<br>
As I got higher level and moved to the west side of the big island (to get 2 vicious), I changed tactics.  I would have regen/skin/coat/lev on, cammo and watch the wanderers and look for blues.  Then I would drop cammo and streak past 4 (including the 2 vicious).  I always took some hits, but nothing to worry about.  It's not too hard, even with their large aggro range, to only aggro 4 if you study the landscape first and pay attention.  Then I would head out over the open waters with my little pack swimming behind me.  It only takes about 30 or 40 seconds to get back to the CB island.  Be careful not to get too far ahead, but they swim damn fast.  I ALWAYS stuck to the west side of CB, because the egress point is on the east side and it's not nice to pop in to 4 angy raptors.  Then would come the most fun part of raptor hunting:  getting all 4 aggroed, speeding raptors snared.  Maxed channeling is essential to cast thru the occasional (or not-so-occasional) hit.  This just takes some practice, hehe.  Then just quad em around the west side of CB island.  The major drawback to this method is that the last surviving vicious will frequently gate before you have time to cast root, sometimes to a spot in the ocean, sometimes all the way back to the big island.  But this is more an aggravation than anything else.<br>
<br>
The only time I ever died doing raptors was from lag/LD.<br>
<br>
I hardly ever solo anymore, and if I never see another raptor again it will be too soon, but they were great exp from 52-57 or so.  And the vicious are blue to 60.<br>
<br>
Duggall<br>
Level 59 Halfling Druid<br>
Morell Thule <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugalianaelessedil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galiana Elessedil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/1/01 7:19:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Quadding</span><hr size=1> Well I stopped being a pansy and went. So far so good. This is what I've worked out so far:<br>
<br>
Park it on a tiny outcropping of rock between the two islands at -8825, 2483. This gives you a place to lev and land without going into water. To my left, which would be the west island, there will be one raptor. I root/rot him with epic/es vambs/breath of ro.<br>
<br>
To my left, the eastern islands, there are 3 raptors on the north side, with a ruined building, two regular and one vicious. On the far side, which would be the eastern point, is a wanderer. I can get all four and quad them along that side of the island safely. So far I've been doing that and getting about a blue bubble with each try, but I always go OOM and have had to bust out the Lumi staff several times.<br>
<br>
So far so good. Better than CS where Wyverns are hunted into extinction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugalianaelessedil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galiana Elessedil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/2/01 12:02:07 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The raptors</span><hr size=1> Boy do I regret being such a puss about this place. Can you say DING!? Finally level 53. No more Vox raids for me. :)<br>
<br>
I really regret now being such a weinie about the islands. They are a lot bigger than I originally thought. I can safely quad in back of the big island but have to be careful to avoid adds. Even with 2 adds I was able to do it thanks to a combo of my Lumi staff, Epic, and rooting.<br>
<br>
At the rate I gained XP I could be level 54 by the end of the holiday. Ahhhh. :) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubadiendruid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BadienDruid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/2/01 8:55:28 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The raptors</span><hr size=1> Raptors rule <p>Badien Bloodletter<br>
55th Preserver of Norath<br>
The Shadow Order<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uelitwo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ELITWO</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.iconbazaar.com/objects/animated/pg19/img14.html" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(9/4/01 8:25:18 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The raptors</span><hr size=1> Quading requires more keyboard dex than this old man has.<br>
<br>
I just dinged 54, and headed out there today.  As the zone is really an ocean, I equiped my enduring breath earring, just in case.  As I approched the isle, a rapter agroed from what felt like a long range, so I root/rotted him out under the ocean.<br>
<br>
Question, what do people think my odds are of &quot;random adds&quot; while root/roting under water?<br>
<br>
Also, anyone know how many hpts these things really have? i was kinda nervous and overnuked, but dont know by how much. <p>CEO of Eli Air.<BR>
Official airline of the Ravens.<BR>
Come Listen to the Sirens in Cobalt Scar.<BR>  Watch the otters playing on the beach. <BR>See dragons breath fire upon the helpless.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/userberus00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Serberus00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/26/01 2:35:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The raptors</span><hr size=1> Is it really possible to quad these at 50?<br>
<br>
I managed to 'quad' two of them and I was OOM with one almost dead, had to DoD it then hit it once.<br>
<br>
I don't have any right clickable gear but i've got 6k to spend, ES vambs a good idea? and lumi staff if I can find one (I know 6k won't cover this)?<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
<br>
Serberus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uabru.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Abru</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/26/01 3:43:32 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The raptors</span><hr size=1> Possible at 50?  Sure.  Worth it?  Maybe not.  You'll consistently end up oom with raptors that aren't dead yet, and spends lots of time finishing them off that you could have spent medding otherwise.  Lumi staff will help, if you can keep from dying while you're blasting them right as they come into mele range.<br>
<br>
Much more doable at 50 if you can procure some kind of mana regen, like c1, c2 or glades.  Glades is especially nice because it lasts two hours, and gives you hp/ac to boot. <p>Abru, Hierophant on The Nameless,  <a href="http://www.legacyofsteel.com/index.shtml" target=_top>Legacy of Steel</a>, <a href="mailto:AbruEQ@hotmail.com">AbruEQ@hotmail.com</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urheawindsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rhea Windsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/26/01 5:25:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The raptors</span><hr size=1> if I remember correctly raptors have close to 4k hp, and viscious have close to 5k. ES arms helped me a ton as I was wisdom-challenged at the time ;) (185 or so) <p><p align="center">
